        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>27 West 16<lb/>
                NY City 28&#47;10&#47;87<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Doctor<lb/></p>
            <p>Enclosed please find letter<lb/> from Mr Blumenthal which please return.<lb/>  When do you propose to have the necessary<lb/> meeting of the Advisory Board&#63;  Thursday is<lb/> a bad day&#44; for Mr Jacobs &#38; my brother cannot come.<lb/>  Sunday is often a wedding day&#44; what about<lb/> Monday&#63;  Then again the notice must be<lb/> sent to the papers&#44; and it is too late for this<lb/> week.  Let me <sic>here</sic> from you.  It is desirable<lb/> that you be present&#44; and necessary.  You might<lb/> if you choose Sunday&#44; see Dr Lieberman or others<lb/> in the morning&#44; or the applicants for admission as<lb/> students.<lb/></p>
            <p>I wrote over a week ago to ask your opinion<lb/> as to 1. cremation&#59; where is authority declaring<lb/> it contrary to Jewish Law and secondly&#44; if a body<lb/> already cremated is brought to us for interment&#44;<lb/> should we inter the ashes in our cemetery.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Will you kindly reply and oblige<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> H. Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
